step_data.thought:
Looking at the current state of the page, I can see that the route is currently showing directions from Central Park (40.7828, -73.9654) to Times Square (40.7570, -73.9860). This is evident from the 'From' and 'To' fields in the interface. My goal is to reverse this direction to show the route from Times Square to Central Park instead.

I notice there is a 'Reverse Directions' button with bid [174] that's currently focused. This button will swap the origin and destination, which is exactly what I need to do to accomplish the goal.

By clicking this button, the 'From' field will change to Times Square coordinates and the 'To' field will change to Central Park coordinates, effectively reversing the direction of the route.
